==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Parakite
<hw>Par"a*kite`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Para-</ets>
+ <ets>kite</ets>.]</ety> <def>A train or series of kites on one string
and flying tandem, used for attaining great heights and for sending up
instruments for meteorological observations or a man for military
reconnaissance; also, a kite of such a train.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

